# kitbag configuration.
#
# Credentials belong in SECURE STORAGE, not here. Run:
#     kitbag configure         # store API keys/tokens in your OS keychain
#     kitbag secrets import    # move any keys already in this file into the store
#
# This file is for non-secret defaults (models, timeouts, directories). You *can* keep
# credentials here if you prefer, but the secure store is recommended.
#
# For a globally installed tool, copy this to ~/.kitbag/.env and fill in what you need.
# A .env in the current directory overrides it per-project; real env vars beat both.
# Resolution order: env var > cwd .env > secure store > ~/.kitbag/.env.

# Credentials (prefer `kitbag configure` over setting these here).
# Required by `kitbag ai-commit` — MiniMax API key used to generate commit messages.
# MINIMAX_API_KEY=

# Required by `kitbag claude-sandbox` — set whichever Claude credential you use.
# (A long-lived token comes from `claude setup-token`.)
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
# CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_TOKEN=

# Secrets backend: auto (keychain if available, else encrypted file) | keyring | file.
# KITBAG_SECRETS_BACKEND=auto
# Passphrase for the encrypted-file backend (only used when the backend is `file`).
# KITBAG_MASTER_PASSPHRASE=
